        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 12:37AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1237 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Fish Creek, or near
Cedartown, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Cedartown, Buchanan, Bremen, Temple, Rockmart, Tallapoosa, Waco,
Braswell, Yorkville, Eubank Lake, Antioch, Van Wert, Draketown, and
Felton.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
